EMERGING DISEASES MASKED BY BACKGROUND
**************************************
A ProMED-mail post
See Also
HIV/AIDS origin 980212200756
[My comment that the first cases of AIDS were likely masked by the
'background noise' of multiple common infections in Africa provoked the
following comments - Mod.JW
[1
From: Richard Frankel <rfrankel@hawaii.edu>
Date: Fri, 13 Feb 1998 05:44:24 -1000

I suspect that the "background noise" of tuberculosis was even more
significant. The effects of HIV on tuberculosis in the U.S. are well
known. Patients in Africa who have AIDS are much less likely than patients
in wealthy countries to die from _Pneumocystis carinii_ infection or from
other opportunistic infections or malignancies and much more likely to die
from tuberculosis. I believe that the background high rate of death from
tuberculosis in Africa contributed to the delay in recognition of HIV.
--
Richard I. Frankel, M.D., M.P.H.
Professor of Medicine
University of Hawaii School of Medicine
