[2
Date: Sun, 15 Feb 1998 13:06:04 -0700
From: Karen Fern Silver <karensilver@mailexcite.com>

My sense is that this is also the case with Ebola and other similar
diseases. The high level of surrounding medical and social pathology that
provides the "noise" of underdeveloped economies might well mask much
that's going on and we don't have sentinel stations around the world to
pick up what's out there.
--
Karen Fern Silver
e-mail: karensilver@mailexcite.com
[ProMED-mail's parent project, ProMED -- the Program for Monitoring
Emerging Diseases -- was set up by the Federation of American Scientists
specifically to promote the development of sentinel stations, but has so
far not attracted any funding. ProMED-mail itself is in a precarious
financial situation - Mod.JW ......................................jw/es
